    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> herby stock </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Once the sauce has slightly thickened, add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped basil</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a very generous crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
